events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: — Under a new coach, with fans packed into the stands for the first time since 2019 and its backup quarterback at the helm, Illinois beat Nebraska 30-22 on Saturday to kick off the 2021 college football season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illinois fends off Nebraska in 30-22 season-opening win

events.name: UConn Huskies at Fresno State Bulldogs
Hawai'i Rainbow Warriors at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: — The mother of UCLA quarterback Dorian Thompson-Robinson echoed the thoughts of many Bruins fans during the first half of Saturday's game against Hawaii after Zach Charbonnet scored his third touchdown.
headlines.shortLinkText: Charbonnet has 3 TDs in UCLA debut as Bruins rout Hawaii

video.headline: UCLA's Charbonnet fights through tackles to score as part of 3-TD game

events.name: UTEP Miners at New Mexico State Aggies

headlines.description: — Jacob Cowing had a career-high 158 yards receiving, including a 59-yard score, and UTEP opened the season with a 30-3 victory over New Mexico State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cowing had career night in UTEP's 30-3 win over Aggies
